Bring a large pan of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp}. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Zest and halve the @lime{1}(zested and halved). Halve the @shiitake mushrooms{50%g}(halved). In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @soy sauce{25%g}, @honey{15%g} and @ketjap manis{25%g}. Line a #baking tray{} with foil and drizzle with oil.

Pop the @sea bass fillets{2} (skin side down) on the foil and pour a tablespoon of the sauce over each fillet. Spread with the back of the spoon to coat the fish. When the water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Pop the fish under the grill and cook until the sauce is caramelising and the fish is cooked, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Once hot, add the @baby corn, greens & carrots{200%g} and shiitake mushrooms. Stir fry until just tender, ~{2%minutes}.

Add the remaining soy mixture with the lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice and a splash of water. Drain the noodles, then add to the pan of vegetables and mix together. Continue to cook until everything is piping hot. Add any remaining sauce too the noodles. Divide the noodles between plates and top with the sea bass. Serve with lime wedges alongside. Enjoy!